				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some of these stacking issues have been around pre-PoP, but it just became very noticable with my newer PoP spells.  It seems like we dont have a single beneficial buff spell that doesnt have some sort of stacking issue.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Heres what Ive found so far, and it seems like I find more every day.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Spiritual Vigor Line :  Will overwrite Brells, Brells will overwrite Vigor,  Wont overwrite Strength of Tunare, SoT will overwrite Vigor.  Vigor is also overwriten by Avatar, and Monk Epic click effect.  Spiritual Vigor Prevents Paladins and Clerics from using the Yaulp line of spells.  Summary, excellent buff, stacking issues make it worthless in any situation other then soloing or being in a group with no paladin or rangers.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Infusion of Spirt :  Prevents most Enchanter haste spells from sticking.  Reasoning, Infusion gives Strength Stamina and Dex, spells like Speed of Vallon also give stamina and dex.  Shamans Focus of Spirit (str dex agi) stacks normally with all enchanter haste spells, solution, swap out of sta for agi, or just correct the coding so it stacks, as is, people get ANGRY with me when I buff them with Infusion of Spirit, because it effectively cuts them off from all the high end haste buffs.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Spiritual Purity Line : Doesnt Stack with Wizard Epic, I think thats bogus, but apparently its by design since its already been patched once and not taken care of then, pheeh!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
This isnt a rant, I love my beastlord, I love his spells.  Im just hoping that maybe posting this will bring it to Verants attention and they will iron out some of the stacking issues. <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
