				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Infusion of spirit aslo has another side affect that you never noticed or mentioned but I have even tested this.
<br />

<br />
If you cast our haste buffs that we can cast, you do not get the intended haste effect your suppose to have. I noticed when I removed IoF that I was swinging far far faster then I did with it on..
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I noticed that if you were to cast your haste buff in the first 3 slots of your buffs, and infusion under it or last on your buff list 50% of the time you get the haste your supose to have.. and 50% of the time your only attacking with your epics 40% speed. Even then so.. I am still woundering are we getting our epic's haste or not, sometimes it seams I am swinging pretty slow.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Just my two cents and views of what Iof is doing. I will contuie to use Iof I wouldnt want to drop 250hp + it gives me. <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
