			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I always thought it was kind of ironic that they want to encourage groups with artificial means (like group xp bonuses) but, at the same time, they discourage them with stacking issues.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I have a daily battle with paladins who keep casting the BMB they have been using forever.  Worse, I can't even say its better all the time.  Monks epic overwrites and so does Clerics Yaulp line so I have half the party wanting SV and half wanting BMB.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Spiritual Purity line is a wonderful exception.  Its not as good as Clarity or bard mana songs...but the fact that it stacks with them makes it particularly useful.  The fact that it has very few stacking issues means I don't have to go through this hassle of asking people to send me tells if their group wants it in a raid.  I just announce its coming around (for the wizards sake) and then buff everyone.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
- Uusk TwoShard
<br />

<br />
65 Iksar BeastLord <i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
